WEBVTT

00:00.507 --> 00:02.212
<i>Previously on</i> Mike & Molly...

00:02.213 --> 00:04.042
Look at you,
writing again.

00:04.043 --> 00:05.343
Yeah, new story.

00:05.344 --> 00:06.343
About a young girl

00:06.345 --> 00:07.879
coming of age
on a hardscrabble farm

00:07.880 --> 00:09.847
at the base
of the Mudlick mountains.

00:09.849 --> 00:11.082
Mudlick? Th-That's weird.

00:11.083 --> 00:13.684
My mom grew up
on a farm in Mudlick.

00:16.187 --> 00:18.489
Oh, no!

00:18.491 --> 00:20.759
I have to see
Mudlick for myself.

00:20.760 --> 00:22.193
When Hemingway
wrote about Paris,

00:22.194 --> 00:23.528
he walked those streets.

00:23.529 --> 00:25.195
It's what made it authentic.

00:25.197 --> 00:27.464
You know, she still has a sister
down in Mudlick.

00:27.466 --> 00:28.932
No! I didn't
know that.

00:28.934 --> 00:31.236
See, that's the kind of stuff
I'm hoping to dig into

00:31.237 --> 00:32.668
when I drag her down there.

00:33.238 --> 00:35.072
Here she is.

00:35.074 --> 00:37.007
Rosie?

00:38.476 --> 00:40.711
You slut! I'll kill you!

00:44.082 --> 00:46.249
Why didn't you ever call me?

00:46.251 --> 00:48.086
Why do you think?

00:48.087 --> 00:49.654
I was wracked with guilt.

00:49.655 --> 00:51.254
I was so stupid.

00:51.256 --> 00:52.990
You were 16.

00:52.991 --> 00:54.791
And stupid.

00:59.697 --> 01:01.833
You know my mom
hates drop-bys.

01:01.834 --> 01:04.068
It's not a drop-by.
It's a check-in.

01:04.069 --> 01:05.803
We haven't heard from
her in two days. Or...

01:05.804 --> 01:07.638
...we haven't
heard from her in two days.

01:07.639 --> 01:09.306
See? It's all in the way you
look at it.

01:09.308 --> 01:11.709
Since when are you so
worried about my mom?

01:11.710 --> 01:13.210
Since we're a month
behind on our book.

01:13.212 --> 01:14.312
After we're done writing,

01:14.313 --> 01:16.480
then let the postman
find her carcass.

01:16.481 --> 01:17.781
Wow.
Or...

01:17.783 --> 01:20.583
...then let
the postman find her carcass.

01:22.386 --> 01:24.121
There you are.

01:24.122 --> 01:26.189
What do you want?

01:26.191 --> 01:28.359
Uh, we're just
checking in on you.

01:28.360 --> 01:29.759
We don't need
to come in.

01:29.761 --> 01:30.461
Good.

01:30.462 --> 01:31.729
Uh...
See?

01:31.730 --> 01:32.963
She's still alive.
Let's go.

01:32.964 --> 01:34.098
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait.

01:34.099 --> 01:35.533
Did you hear that
music playing in there?

01:35.534 --> 01:37.334
Yeah. So?
She hates music.

01:37.335 --> 01:38.969
Unless it's coming
out of a pipe organ,

01:38.970 --> 01:40.738
she calls it "ear rape."

01:40.739 --> 01:43.873
Well, she uses that word a lot
when she really shouldn't.

01:43.875 --> 01:46.042
There's something
going on in there.

01:46.044 --> 01:48.178
Come on, Scooby-Doo,
let's not meddle.

01:48.179 --> 01:49.279
No... Is it a fella?

01:49.280 --> 01:50.948
Do you think she has
a fella in there?

01:50.949 --> 01:52.449
We have a book to finish.

01:52.450 --> 01:54.651
I don't have time for her
to go tom-catting around.

01:54.652 --> 01:56.253
"Fella?" "Tom-catting""

01:56.254 --> 01:58.955
You are spending too much
time with the elderly.

01:58.957 --> 02:00.491
What?

02:00.492 --> 02:01.491
Listen, Peggy,

02:01.493 --> 02:02.993
when we're done with the book,

02:02.994 --> 02:05.462
you can pitch woo with as many
gentleman callers as you'd like.

02:05.463 --> 02:07.930
But right now,
we got work to do.

02:07.932 --> 02:09.499
What are you talking about?

02:09.501 --> 02:11.401
Molly thinks you
got a guy in there.

02:11.402 --> 02:12.870
Who is it, Margaret?

02:12.871 --> 02:15.371
No judgment, Ma.
Have a nice time.

02:15.373 --> 02:17.841
Rosemary!

02:17.842 --> 02:20.043
Mike, this is
my sister, Rosemary.

02:20.044 --> 02:21.511
Rosemary,
your nephew, Mike.

02:21.512 --> 02:23.112
All right, good night.

02:23.114 --> 02:25.248
Aw, how about that?

02:25.249 --> 02:27.483
I finally got
to meet my aunt.

