02:58.934 --> 03:00.933
And here's your cousin Colby.

03:00.934 --> 03:03.902
Only one of my six
who made it out of Mudlick.

03:03.904 --> 03:07.273
Lives in Plattsville,
five miles up the road.

03:07.274 --> 03:10.276
Hard to resist
the pull of a big city.

03:10.277 --> 03:12.545
Oh, I just can't
get over you.

03:12.546 --> 03:16.249
You got that chiseled jaw
and strong shoulders

03:16.250 --> 03:17.783
just like your grandma.

03:17.784 --> 03:18.951
Really?

03:18.952 --> 03:20.653
All my mom ever told me
about my shoulders

03:20.654 --> 03:22.654
is they almost killed her
on the way out.

03:22.656 --> 03:26.392
It was like giving birth
to a 14-pound biplane.

03:26.393 --> 03:30.296
I bet you were
a roly-poly lump of lovin'.

03:30.297 --> 03:32.431
I guess, yeah.

03:32.432 --> 03:34.066
Peggy, why didn't you tell us

03:34.067 --> 03:36.267
that Rosemary was coming
for a visit?

03:36.269 --> 03:38.671
I just wanted to make sure
she and I could both stand

03:38.672 --> 03:40.271
to be in the
same room together.

03:40.273 --> 03:42.441
Let the alphas sniff
each other's behinds

03:42.442 --> 03:45.311
before we let the rest
of the pack in.

03:45.312 --> 03:48.147
So, is everything...

03:48.148 --> 03:50.081
smelling okay?

03:50.083 --> 03:54.853
Well, the few whiffs we've had
have been downright pleasant.

03:54.854 --> 03:56.255
Oh, yeah.

03:56.256 --> 03:59.291
We were just playing records
and talking about old times.

03:59.292 --> 04:02.661
Remember seeing Patsy
Cline at the State Fair?

04:02.662 --> 04:05.064
I never went to the State Fair.

04:05.065 --> 04:06.098
Oh, that's right.

04:06.099 --> 04:07.499
Daddy just took me.

04:07.500 --> 04:09.000
You must have
been too young.

04:09.002 --> 04:11.402
Too young for rides
and cotton candy?

04:11.404 --> 04:12.604
Oh!

04:12.605 --> 04:15.874
Oh, there she is
after all these years.

04:15.875 --> 04:17.875
"Little Peggy
cries a lot.

04:17.877 --> 04:20.345
Always wants what
she don't got""

04:21.414 --> 04:22.881
I love that!

04:23.850 --> 04:25.416
You know, that it rhymes.

04:27.753 --> 04:29.254
All that's in the past.

04:29.255 --> 04:33.692
I'm just thankful I finally
got to meet this big, sweet

04:33.693 --> 04:34.860
honey bear!

04:34.861 --> 04:36.528
Oh!

04:36.529 --> 04:37.896
Wow, Molly,
now that's a hug.

04:37.897 --> 04:39.865
- You got to get in on this.
- I know.

04:39.866 --> 04:40.999
I had one in Mudlick.

04:41.000 --> 04:42.868
It's like rolling
in a pile of puppies.

04:42.869 --> 04:44.269
Oh, get in here!

04:44.270 --> 04:46.571
Oh!

04:46.572 --> 04:48.405
I'm good.

04:52.477 --> 04:54.546
When I met Aunt Rosemary,

04:54.547 --> 04:56.248
there was
an immediate connection.

04:56.249 --> 04:57.716
It's like we always
knew each other.

04:57.717 --> 04:59.917
I've never felt that way
about another person.

05:04.756 --> 05:06.591
Really?

05:06.592 --> 05:07.759
No one else?

05:07.760 --> 05:09.961
Ah, Carl.

05:09.962 --> 05:12.564
You just be careful with
this so-called aunt.

05:12.565 --> 05:14.065
What are you talking about?

05:14.066 --> 05:16.734
The only long-lost relative that
I ever came into contact with

05:16.735 --> 05:19.770
was some shady cousin
who wanted my kidney.

05:23.675 --> 05:25.409
She's not like that.

05:25.411 --> 05:26.577
Oh, you say that now,
but wait until you wake up

05:26.578 --> 05:27.979
in the middle of the night

05:27.980 --> 05:30.147
and she's drawing on your
stomach with a magic marker.

05:32.016 --> 05:33.318
Don't be ridiculous.

05:33.319 --> 05:35.286
Aunt Rosemary is sweet,
caring, understanding.

05:35.287 --> 05:36.721
And her hugs... oh.

05:36.722 --> 05:38.289
Nothing like hugging my mom.

05:38.290 --> 05:40.091
Yeah.

05:40.092 --> 05:41.359
Yeah, I hugged
your mom before.

05:41.360 --> 05:43.161
Like squeezing
a scarecrow.

05:43.162 --> 05:45.496
At least a scarecrow's warm

05:45.497 --> 05:47.398
from spending all day
in the sun.

05:48.801 --> 05:51.101
I just can't believe
those two women are sisters.

05:51.103 --> 05:52.904
Hey, what are you guys
talking about?

05:52.905 --> 05:55.373
Ah, I finally got
to meet my mother's sister.

05:55.374 --> 05:57.007
Does she want a kidney?

05:58.743 --> 06:01.344
No!

06:02.713 --> 06:04.815
my aunt is so loving

06:04.816 --> 06:07.852
it makes me wonder
how I would've turned out

06:07.853 --> 06:09.754
- if I was raised by her.
- Mm.

06:09.755 --> 06:12.456
See, now, that's classic
nature versus nurture.

06:12.457 --> 06:14.425
Now, are you are who you
are because of genetics,

06:14.426 --> 06:16.960
or are you the product
of your surroundings?

06:16.962 --> 06:18.429
See, I think
with a loving mother,

06:18.430 --> 06:19.730
he would have been
more confident.

06:19.731 --> 06:21.132
And more successful.

06:21.133 --> 06:22.999
Certainly thinner.

06:25.035 --> 06:27.805
And definitely better friends.

06:27.806 --> 06:29.073
Very snippy.

06:29.074 --> 06:30.974
See, that's learned
behavior right there.

06:36.380 --> 06:37.981
You know,
maybe for our vacation,

06:37.982 --> 06:39.416
we should go down to Mudlick.

06:39.417 --> 06:40.984
Mm, yeah, no.

06:40.985 --> 06:41.952
I've been there.

06:41.953 --> 06:44.655
It's not just a pretty name.

06:44.656 --> 06:46.156
So get this.

06:46.157 --> 06:47.424
I'm in the squad car today,

06:47.425 --> 06:48.592
and my cell phone rings.

06:48.593 --> 06:49.626
It's my mom's number,

06:49.627 --> 06:51.394
so I immediately get
that pit in my stomach.

06:51.396 --> 06:54.731
Ooh, the "Peggy pit," yeah.

06:54.732 --> 06:56.333
So I start thinking of excuses,

06:56.334 --> 06:58.602
you know, to cut the call short:
bad reception,

06:58.603 --> 07:00.504
or in the middle
of chasing an illegal.

07:00.505 --> 07:01.605
Ooh, that's a good one.

07:01.606 --> 07:03.373
Hitting her in the sweet spot.

07:03.374 --> 07:04.408
Yeah, but I didn't need to.

07:04.409 --> 07:05.709
Turns out it was
my Aunt Rosemary,

07:05.710 --> 07:06.710
just calling to say hi.

07:06.711 --> 07:07.678
No guilt trips,

07:07.679 --> 07:08.978
no complaining
about the neighbors.

07:08.980 --> 07:11.081
Just wanted to know
how my day was going.

07:11.082 --> 07:12.382
That is so nice.

07:12.383 --> 07:13.817
I know!

07:13.818 --> 07:15.619
D-Don't get me wrong,

07:15.620 --> 07:17.387
I love my mother,
blah, blah, blah.

07:17.388 --> 07:19.189
But can you
imagine growing up

07:19.190 --> 07:21.158
with a mom
like Rosemary?

07:21.159 --> 07:23.460
I tried. It's too painful.

07:23.461 --> 07:25.195
I didn't want to say
anything, but I snuck out

07:25.196 --> 07:27.196
and had coffee with her
this morning.

07:27.198 --> 07:29.232
Why didn't you call me?
You were at work.

07:29.233 --> 07:31.667
I'm sure we could've found
a crime nearby.

07:31.669 --> 07:32.969
I just wanted
to give her

07:32.970 --> 07:34.604
a few chapters of me
and Peggy's book to read.

07:34.605 --> 07:36.172
You know, get a fresh
view on Mudlick

07:36.173 --> 07:38.074
from a current
Mudlicker.

07:38.075 --> 07:39.509
I'll bet she'll love it.

07:39.510 --> 07:41.277
She'll tell you
you did a wonderful job,

07:41.278 --> 07:44.147
and if people don't like it,
they're just jealous.

07:44.148 --> 07:46.916
God, I wish I heard
that growing up.

07:46.917 --> 07:49.586
All I got was "find out if
your teacher thinks I'm hot""

