07:58.795 --> 08:00.063
Hi, Peggy.

08:00.064 --> 08:01.297
What are you
doing here?

08:01.298 --> 08:02.665
Oh, we were just in
the neighborhood,

08:02.666 --> 08:04.500
thought we'd stop
and see Aunt Rosemary.

08:04.501 --> 08:05.468
And you.

08:05.469 --> 08:08.104
'Cause you're here, too.

08:08.105 --> 08:09.939
You didn't call ahead,

08:09.940 --> 08:12.575
so no warning, no bra,
no complaints.

08:12.576 --> 08:15.445
No problem, no looking.

08:15.446 --> 08:17.547
Oh, hey, Molly.
Hey!

08:17.548 --> 08:19.749
There's my sweet nephew.

08:19.750 --> 08:21.717
Oh! Ooh!

08:21.718 --> 08:23.619
Ooh, we're stuck.

08:23.620 --> 08:24.921
I can't let go.

08:24.922 --> 08:26.556
I don't know what
we're gonna do.

08:26.557 --> 08:29.124
I guess we'll just
have to keep hugging!

08:29.126 --> 08:32.027
All right, break it up.
This ain't France.

08:32.029 --> 08:34.530
Oh, thank you
for letting me read this.

08:34.530 --> 08:36.899
Some very interesting things
in here.

08:36.900 --> 08:38.267
In where?

08:38.268 --> 08:40.269
I gave her the last few
chapters of our book.

08:40.270 --> 08:42.171
What'd you do that for?

08:42.172 --> 08:44.206
Well, it might be
your life story, Peggy,

08:44.207 --> 08:45.474
but she lived it, too.

08:45.475 --> 08:48.811
I'm sorry, dear,
but I didn't live any of this.

08:48.812 --> 08:50.546
And you didn't
either, Peggy.

08:50.547 --> 08:51.914
What are you
talking about?

08:51.915 --> 08:53.516
Every word in
there is true.

08:53.517 --> 08:55.016
Oh, nonsense.

08:55.018 --> 08:57.119
You make it out
like we were raised in hell

08:57.120 --> 08:58.753
by the Devil himself.

08:58.755 --> 09:00.756
That farm <i> was</i> my hell.

09:00.757 --> 09:03.759
All I know
is you'll never be happy

09:03.760 --> 09:06.428
if you only look
at the negative in things.

09:06.429 --> 09:07.930
I see what I see.

09:07.931 --> 09:11.500
At least I'm not some Pollyanna
living in denial.

09:11.501 --> 09:14.736
All right, ladies,
let's not argue.

09:14.738 --> 09:18.373
Yeah, let's just go put on our
bras and have a nice visit.

09:18.375 --> 09:20.075
Look, if you want
to blame the world

09:20.076 --> 09:22.077
for how you turned out,
that's your business.

09:22.078 --> 09:25.013
But based on what I read, we
grew up in two different houses.

09:25.014 --> 09:26.815
So I'm a liar?
No.

09:26.816 --> 09:28.417
You're bitter and spiteful,

09:28.418 --> 09:31.420
and you have no one to blame
for who you are but yourself.

09:31.421 --> 09:33.522
Get out!

09:33.523 --> 09:36.158
Peggy.

09:36.159 --> 09:37.826
Happy to.

09:39.562 --> 09:41.495
What is wrong with you?

09:41.497 --> 09:42.965
Only you could manage
to throw the nicest woman

09:42.966 --> 09:44.265
in the world out of your house.

09:44.267 --> 09:47.002
If she's so wonderful,
why don't you join her?

09:47.003 --> 09:48.337
Ugh, alienate everybody, Ma.

09:48.338 --> 09:50.605
That's why all your stories end
with you alone.

09:50.606 --> 09:52.808
I'm gonna go help her pack;
she can stay with us.

09:52.809 --> 09:54.376
Come on.

09:54.377 --> 09:57.979
Peggy, you don't want
your sister to leave.

09:57.980 --> 09:59.648
She's not my sister.

09:59.649 --> 10:01.582
I don't have a sister anymore.

10:05.453 --> 10:07.955
You go see if she's okay.

10:11.826 --> 10:14.028
I get it.

10:26.377 --> 10:29.013
More fresh biscuits.

10:29.014 --> 10:30.948
Who's ready?

10:30.949 --> 10:33.449
I'd love to,
but sadly I'm full.

10:35.252 --> 10:38.455
Oh, wait, it was just the table
cinching my stomach.

10:38.456 --> 10:40.623
I got room.

10:41.892 --> 10:44.561
No offense, Mom,
but I did not realize until now

10:44.562 --> 10:46.063
what a horrible
cook you are.

10:46.064 --> 10:47.364
Oh...

10:47.365 --> 10:48.732
none taken.

10:48.733 --> 10:50.634
Rosemary, I know
this is sudden,

10:50.635 --> 10:53.569
but will you marry us?

10:54.738 --> 10:56.406
I'd get down on one knee,
but at this point

10:56.407 --> 10:59.175
I don't think I'd be able
to get back up again.

10:59.177 --> 11:01.878
That's flattering,
but the only threesome I know

11:01.879 --> 11:05.015
that ever worked were
the Father, Son and Holy Ghost.

11:05.016 --> 11:07.883
Let's agree to disagree.

11:10.854 --> 11:12.289
Mike, come on.

11:12.290 --> 11:14.825
I just think it would be a good
idea if you made up with her.

11:14.826 --> 11:16.293
She's your mother.

11:16.294 --> 11:18.595
Oh, no, you're just trying to
throw me into the lion's den

11:18.596 --> 11:20.797
so she doesn't
eat you alive.

11:20.798 --> 11:23.099
Yes!

11:23.100 --> 11:25.434
She's miserable
even when she's happy.

11:25.436 --> 11:27.537
Look, I could spend all
day worrying about her,

11:27.538 --> 11:30.540
or I can enjoy the day
getting to know my aunt.

11:30.541 --> 11:33.510
One is causing me grief,
one is making me pancakes.

11:33.511 --> 11:36.212
It ain't exactly
<i> Sophie's Choice.</i>

11:36.213 --> 11:38.747
Vince, tap out! I'm up!

11:43.319 --> 11:45.388
Maybe we should start going
over some of the stuff

11:45.389 --> 11:46.723
we've already written.

11:46.724 --> 11:49.459
You know, just make sure
it still rings true.

11:49.460 --> 11:51.895
So you think I'm a liar, too.

11:51.896 --> 11:53.596
Wha...?

11:53.597 --> 11:54.831
No, I don't.

11:54.832 --> 11:56.900
But memory is
a funny thing.

11:56.901 --> 11:58.934
You know, last week,
I could've sworn

11:58.936 --> 12:00.870
that I pulled that nozzle
out of the gas tank

12:00.871 --> 12:02.372
before I drove away.

12:02.373 --> 12:03.640
And then I get home,

12:03.641 --> 12:07.243
and I see ten feet of hose
dangling from my car,

12:07.244 --> 12:11.546
and I had to tell myself,
"I may have remembered wrong."

12:12.582 --> 12:16.318
Hey, you may be an idiot,
but I'm not a liar.

12:18.121 --> 12:19.822
You know, I'm trying
to help you here.

12:19.823 --> 12:21.157
You make it very hard.

12:21.158 --> 12:22.925
I don't need help
from anybody.

12:22.926 --> 12:25.194
Let's just finish the damn book
and be done with it.

12:25.195 --> 12:26.896
Fine.
This is my story.

12:26.897 --> 12:28.531
I know what went on
in that house.

12:28.532 --> 12:30.199
You lived it.
Exactly.

12:30.200 --> 12:33.336
Let's just forget about
Rosemary and get writing.

12:33.337 --> 12:34.737
Great.

12:34.738 --> 12:37.239
Rosemary was always
the perfect one.

12:37.240 --> 12:38.941
Always said
the right thing,

12:38.942 --> 12:39.909
got good grades.

12:39.910 --> 12:41.544
You know what it's like
to grow up

12:41.545 --> 12:43.812
in the shadow
of a sister like that?

12:45.081 --> 12:47.348
I kind of am that sister.

12:49.185 --> 12:51.120
Maybe I was to blame.

12:51.121 --> 12:53.856
I never made it easy
for people to love me.

12:53.857 --> 12:56.525
Daddy said I was born sour.

12:56.526 --> 12:58.994
I guess he was right.

12:58.995 --> 13:00.396
You're not sour.

13:00.397 --> 13:04.433
You're... tangy.

13:04.434 --> 13:05.768
Don't sugarcoat it.

13:05.769 --> 13:07.636
I'm a big pain in the ass.

13:07.637 --> 13:10.505
Nobody wants
to be around that.

13:18.680 --> 13:21.283
Ah, I got to stop
feeling sorry for myself.

13:21.284 --> 13:22.784
We got a book
to write.

13:22.785 --> 13:27.189
You know what, if it helps,
I do believe you.

13:27.190 --> 13:28.557
Thanks.

13:28.558 --> 13:30.057
It doesn't.

13:32.494 --> 13:35.029
There's that tang!

13:42.771 --> 13:44.039
Watch his cowlick.

13:44.040 --> 13:46.108
That thing loves to pop
up like a prairie dog.

13:47.410 --> 13:49.411
You know, we're supposed
to spend the day together,

13:49.412 --> 13:50.946
not run my errands.

13:50.947 --> 13:52.914
Oh, honey, this
is a joy for me.

13:52.915 --> 13:56.218
Taking care of my nephew,
seeing where he works.

13:56.219 --> 13:57.953
Boy, they sure did love you
down at the precinct.

13:57.954 --> 13:59.121
The captain of the SWAT team

13:59.122 --> 14:01.523
wants your recipe
for snickerdoodles.

14:01.524 --> 14:04.326
I can't believe all those boys
thought I was your mother.

14:04.327 --> 14:08.196
I look nothing like her.

14:08.197 --> 14:11.333
Well, I think the confusion is
that they've never met her.

14:11.334 --> 14:13.234
Ten years on the force,

14:13.235 --> 14:15.537
and you never brought Peggy
to see where you work?

14:15.538 --> 14:17.706
Well, they like me there;
I don't want to mess that up.

14:18.708 --> 14:20.475
You know,
it's a shame it took us

14:20.476 --> 14:22.644
all these years to
finally connect.

14:22.645 --> 14:24.612
Yeah, you'd think Mom could have
swallowed her pride

14:24.613 --> 14:26.948
and took me down there
to meet you just once.

14:26.949 --> 14:28.616
Well, don't be
too hard on her.

14:28.617 --> 14:31.352
She's always
been stubborn.

14:31.353 --> 14:32.987
And holds a grudge, too.

14:32.988 --> 14:34.422
A lady at church
made the mistake

14:34.423 --> 14:36.157
of buying the same hat
as her.

14:36.158 --> 14:37.959
She glared at her every Sunday

14:37.960 --> 14:41.062
until that woman
became a Lutheran.

14:41.063 --> 14:43.064
Oh, I know all about
that side of her.

14:43.065 --> 14:45.733
The Christmas I got a bike,
she got sheets for her bed.

14:45.734 --> 14:47.568
You'd think
the world was ending.

14:47.569 --> 14:51.773
Well, um, sheets are kind of
a crappy Christmas present.

14:51.774 --> 14:54.075
Yeah, that's what
"Peggy cries-a-lot" said.

14:54.076 --> 14:55.576
Felt so sorry
for herself.

14:55.577 --> 14:58.246
If we hadn't ignored
her little pity party,

14:58.247 --> 15:01.048
it would've ruined Christmas
for everybody.

15:01.049 --> 15:04.318
Well, wasn't Christmas
kind of ruined for her?

15:04.319 --> 15:06.254
Well, it was her own fault.

15:06.255 --> 15:08.322
If she'd just smiled
every once in a while

15:08.323 --> 15:10.958
and appreciated
what she did have,

15:10.959 --> 15:12.927
maybe I wouldn't have
been the only one

15:12.928 --> 15:14.261
Daddy took to Patsy Cline

15:14.262 --> 15:17.497
or gave a horse to
for graduating grade school.

15:17.499 --> 15:20.968
Well, that doesn't
seem exactly fair.

15:20.969 --> 15:23.604
Well, life ain't fair.

15:23.605 --> 15:25.606
That's what Daddy
always told Peggy.

15:25.607 --> 15:28.242
And if she ain't learned
that yet, she never will.

15:28.243 --> 15:30.244
That explains a lot.

15:30.245 --> 15:32.213
My goodness.

15:32.214 --> 15:36.082
With this buzz cut, you look
even more like your grandma.

15:38.953 --> 15:40.955
Peggy, don't get
down about today.

15:40.956 --> 15:43.691
Some days, you give
me 20 pages of gold,

15:43.692 --> 15:46.627
and, well, sometimes you...

15:46.628 --> 15:50.297
The point is, just don't get
too down about it.

15:50.298 --> 15:51.899
I'm not.

15:51.900 --> 15:53.433
I blame you.

15:55.903 --> 15:57.571
Hey.

15:57.572 --> 15:59.006
What do you want?

15:59.007 --> 16:01.608
To talk.

16:01.609 --> 16:03.744
Can you give us
a minute, sweetie?

16:03.745 --> 16:05.512
Oh. Yeah, sure.

16:05.513 --> 16:08.414
I'll... I'll just be
in the kitchen.

16:09.883 --> 16:12.084
I am gonna listen. I just...

16:14.154 --> 16:16.956
I just want to be
up front about that.

16:20.727 --> 16:22.029
Listen, uh...

16:22.030 --> 16:24.698
I-I don't want to rehash
what happened last night.

16:24.699 --> 16:28.735
You mean where you backstabbed
me by siding with my sister?

16:28.736 --> 16:31.938
Yeah, that's the part
I didn't want to rehash.

16:31.939 --> 16:33.640
I saw how you were
with her.

16:33.641 --> 16:34.674
Ma...

16:34.675 --> 16:36.776
No, I get it.

16:36.777 --> 16:39.446
Rosemary's easy to love,
always has been.

16:39.447 --> 16:42.983
But we are who we are.

16:42.984 --> 16:45.118
It's not your fault.
No?

16:45.119 --> 16:47.787
Maybe it is,
but I don't care.

16:47.788 --> 16:51.291
I might be a tough
nasty piece of gristle,

16:51.292 --> 16:54.961
but whatever I was, whatever
I did, somehow it made you.

16:54.962 --> 16:57.496
And I wouldn't change that
for the world.

16:59.866 --> 17:01.867
Neither would I.

17:10.310 --> 17:12.377
There you go,
now squeeze.

17:12.378 --> 17:14.012
I feel ridiculous.

17:17.317 --> 17:19.719
You'll get used to it.

17:19.720 --> 17:22.722
Incoming!

17:34.050 --> 17:38.019
All right, and this
is our precinct room.

17:38.021 --> 17:39.388
Everybody, this
is my mother.

17:39.390 --> 17:41.157
Well, who was
the other lady?

17:41.158 --> 17:43.759
Like I said,<i> this</i>
is my mother.

17:43.761 --> 17:45.695
Hey.

17:45.696 --> 17:47.629
Which one's Kilpatrick?

17:47.631 --> 17:49.165
He always gives me
the brush off

17:49.166 --> 17:51.300
when I call about
the hippie neighbors.

17:51.301 --> 17:54.302
Always parking their commie
Prius in front of my house.

17:54.304 --> 17:56.571
Uh, yeah, he-he's
got the day off.

17:57.406 --> 17:59.509
Nice to see you,
Mother Biggs.

17:59.510 --> 18:00.843
Hello, Carlton.

18:03.179 --> 18:05.081
Oh, somebody's
been practicing.

18:06.116 --> 18:08.883
Okay, it's not
a dance marathon.

18:08.885 --> 18:10.219
All right, we
should get going.

18:10.220 --> 18:11.887
We need to get you
your mug shot,

18:11.888 --> 18:14.289
and let you badger the drunks
down in the holding tank.

18:14.291 --> 18:16.191
You are good
to your mother.

